**Item:** SCP-8536

**Containment Class:** Safe

**Containment Protocols:** Item 8536 is to be contained at Facility 04 in a designated humanoid containment chamber. Personnel assigned to Item 8536 must rotate on a bi-weekly basis to minimize prolonged exposure to the Item's secondary anomalous property. All Foundation staff presenting symptoms consistent with the Item's secondary anomalous property are to be referred to psychological evaluation without exception.

**Description:** Item 8536 is a human male of Caucasian descent, approximately 20 years of age. The words "Mr. Watches, from Little Misters ® by Dr. Wondertainment" is tattooed on the Item's right outer wrist. Item 8536 presents a mustache structurally analogous to the hands of a clock: the left end corresponds to the minute hand and the right end to the hour hand, joined at a single central point located immediately above the upper lip, functioning as an axis. Both ends rotate clockwise along this axis autonomously, maintaining accurate correspondence to local time at all times.

Item 8536 is also capable of producing an auditory output acoustically similar to that of a standard wall clock. Radiological examination has revealed a metallic mechanism occupying the thoracic cavity of Item 8536. This mechanism is theorized to be the source of the aforementioned auditory output; its precise function and operational purpose remain undetermined. 

Item 8536 presents observable signs of sentience and retains capacity for locomotion; however, the Item exhibits a condition consistent with locked-in syndrome [[footnote]] Locked-in syndrome is a condition where a person experiences quadriplegia and bulbar palsy due to damage in the brainstem. Cognition and vertical eye movements are preserved in many patients. Survivors of this condition often experience debilitating motor loss. [[/footnote]], with the exception that ocular mobility is unrestricted. The Item's eyes have been consistently observed to track individuals within its immediate vicinity. Repeated attempts to elicit responses to external stimuli and establish communication with Item 8536 have produced no measurable results, and the Item is currently assessed as non-communicative. 

A secondary anomalous property is suspected, based on reports submitted by Facility 04 personnel who entered Item 8536's field of view, whether intentionally or otherwise. Affected individuals have reported a persistent sensation of being observed while in isolation, including at private residences and locations geographically distant from Facility 04. Investigation of this property is ongoing.

**Acquisition:**  Item 8536 was discovered on ██/██/2023 at ████████ Primary School, ████████, following a report filed by Teacher Vincent Connor describing an unidentified individual located within a disused storage room on school grounds. Subsequent investigation determined that Item 8536 had occupied the storage room for approximately one week prior to discovery, during which time six students between the ages of 7 and 9 had been accessing the location during recess periods without staff knowledge. Foundation personnel intercepted Mr. Connor's police report and effected containment of Item 8536 without further civilian involvement. Mr. Connor was interviewed and subsequently administered Class-A amnestics. The six students were administered Class-A amnestics and provided a cover narrative attributing their experiences to a shared imaginary construct. At the time of acquisition, Item 8536 was found wearing green suspender pants, a white dress shirt, and a bronze-colored suit jacket, with 'Doctor's Orders' sewn into all garment tags. Three distinct wrist watches were present on the Item's person, alongside its corresponding Little Mister list (see Document 8536/A).

